:ITN046 :hasManagementAdvice "Monitor INR closely and reduce warfarin dose if necessary." .
:ITN046 :hasInteractionDescription "It has been reported that comazole may displace the anticoagulant warfarin. Careful control of the anticoagulant therapy during treatment with Comazole is advisable." .

:ITN047 :interactsWith :S035 .
:ITN047 :hasManagementAdvice "Monitor serum phenytoin levels and signs of toxicity. Dose adjustment may be required." .
:ITN047 :hasInteractionDescription "Comazole also may inhibit the hepatic metabolism of phenytoin. A 39% increase in phenytoin half-life and 27% decrease in the metabolic clearance rate of phenytoin have been observed following administration of Comazole of normal clinical dosages. If these two drugs are given concurrently it is important to remain alert for signs of phenytoin toxicity." .
:ITN047 :hasReference :R031 .

:ITN048 :hasInteractionDescription "Concurrent use of rifampicin and Comazole results in shortening of plasma half life of trimethoprim." .
:ITN048 :interactsWith :S036 .
:ITN048 :hasReference :R031 .
:ITN048 :hasManagementAdvice "Monitor clinical response as trimethoprim levels may be reduced. Consider alternative therapy." .

