:ITN235 :hasClinicalEffects "Concomitant administration of cefixime and nifedipine increases oral bioavailability of cefixime as a result of higher Cmax and AUC." .
:ITN235 :interactsWith :S163 .

:ITN236 :hasManagementAdvice "Not Specified" .
:ITN236 :hasReference :R128 .
:ITN236 :hasClinicalEffects "Concomitant administration of probenecid reportedly increases Cmax and AUC of cefixime and decreases renal clearance and volume of distribution of the drug." .
:ITN236 :interactsWith :S028 .
:ITN236 :hasInteractionDescription "Increases Cmax and AUC of cefixime and decreases renal clearance and volume of distribution of the drug." .

:ITN237 :hasInteractionDescription "Elevated carbamazepine levels" .
:ITN237 :hasManagementAdvice "Drug monitoring when these drugs are given together is advised." .
:ITN237 :hasClinicalEffects "Elevated carbamazepine levels have been reported when administered concomitantly with cefixime." .
:ITN237 :hasReference :R129 .
:ITN237 :interactsWith :S161 .

:ITN238 :hasReference :R129 .
:ITN238 :hasInteractionDescription "In vitro and in vivo antagonism have been noted between cephalosporins and chloramphenicol against a variety of Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria" .
:ITN238 :hasManagementAdvice "it is recommended that combined therapy with chloramphenicol and a cephalosporin be avoided, particularly when bactericidal activity is considered important." .
:ITN238 :interactsWith :S162 .
:ITN238 :hasClinicalEffects "In vitro and in vivo antagonism have been noted between cephalosporins and chloramphenicol against a variety of Gram-positive and Gram-negative bacteria" .

:ITN239 :hasInteractionDescription "Increases oral bioavailability of cefixime" .
:ITN239 :hasManagementAdvice "Not Specified" .
:ITN239 :hasReference :R129 .
:ITN239 :interactsWith :S163 .
:ITN239 :hasClinicalEffects "Higher Cmax and AUC" .

:ITN240 :interactsWith :S146 .
:ITN240 :hasManagementAdvice "Not Specified" .
:ITN240 :hasInteractionDescription "Concomitant administration of probenecid reportedly increases Cmax and AUC of cefixime and decreases renal clearance and volume of distribution of the drug." .
:ITN240 :hasReference :R129 .
:ITN240 :hasClinicalEffects "Concomitant administration of probenecid reportedly increases Cmax and AUC of cefixime and decreases renal clearance and volume of distribution of the drug." .

:ITN241 :hasReference :R129 .
:ITN241 :hasClinicalEffects "Increased prothrombin time, with or without clinical bleeding, has been reported when cefixime is given concomitantly." .
:ITN241 :interactsWith :S164 .
:ITN241 :hasInteractionDescription "Increased prothrombin time, with or without clinical bleeding, has been reported when cefixime is given concomitantly." .
:ITN241 :hasManagementAdvice "Not Specified" .

