:SP001 :hasReference :R022 .
:SP001 :hasStewardshipDescription "Use Monurol only for confirmed uncomplicated urinary tract infections in adult women. Do not use for kidney infections or perinephric abscess." .
:SP001 :hasReference :R023 .

:SP002 :hasReference :R023 .
:SP002 :hasReference :R022 .
:SP002 :hasStewardshipDescription "Avoid unnecessary use to prevent deveopment of antibiotic-resistant bacteria." .

:SP003 :hasStewardshipDescription "Take the full single-dose as instructed. Do not repeat the dose unless prescribed by a doctor." .
:SP003 :hasReference :R023 .
:SP003 :hasReference :R022 .

:SP004 :hasStewardshipDescription "Contact your doctor if symptoms do not improve within 2-3 days. Watch for severe diarrhea, allergic reactions, or worsening urinary symptoms." .
:SP004 :hasReference :R022 .
:SP004 :hasReference :R023 .

:SP005 :hasStewardshipDescription "Do not use in children under 12 years old." .
:SP005 :hasReference :R022 .
:SP005 :hasReference :R023 .

:SP006 :hasReference :R023 .
:SP006 :hasReference :R022 .
:SP006 :hasStewardshipDescription "Pregnant or breastfeeding women should consult their doctor before taking Monurol." .

:SP007 :hasStewardshipDescription "Fosfomycin Tromethamine  should be used only for uncomplicated urinary tract infections caused by E.coli or Enterococcus faecalis. Do not use for pyelonephritis or other infections." .
:SP007 :hasReference :R024 .

:SP008 :hasReference :R024 .
:SP008 :hasStewardshipDescription "Only a single oral dose is recommended. Repeating daily doses does not improve effectiveness and increases side effects." .

:SP009 :hasStewardshipDescription "Obtain urine culture before treatment to ensure the bacteria are susceptible." .
:SP009 :hasReference :R024 .

:SP010 :hasReference :R024 .
:SP010 :hasStewardshipDescription "Patients should take the full dose as instructed and dissolve the powder in water before drinking." .

:SP011 :hasReference :R024 .
:SP011 :hasStewardshipDescription "Monitor symptoms; if they do not improve within 2-3 days or if they return, contact a healthcare provider for further evaluation" .

:SP012 :hasStewardshipDescription "Monitor for diarrhea or water or bloody stools after antibiotic use, which could indicate C. difficile infection." .
:SP012 :hasReference :R024 .

:SP013 :hasReference :R037 .
:SP013 :hasStewardshipDescription "Store at temperatures not exceeding 30°C" .

:SP014 :hasReference :R026 .
:SP014 :hasStewardshipDescription "Use IV fosfomycin only for confirmed or strongly suspected bacterial infections. It should not be used for viral infections." .

:SP015 :hasStewardshipDescription "Reserve IV fosfomycin for serious infections or resistant bacteriawhen other antibiotics are not effective." .
:SP015 :hasReference :R026 .

:SP016 :hasStewardshipDescription "Adjust dose based on kidney function to avoid toxicity." .
:SP016 :hasReference :R026 .

:SP017 :hasReference :R026 .
:SP017 :hasStewardshipDescription "Monitor kidney function during treatment, especially in patients with renal impairment." .

:SP018 :hasReference :R026 .
:SP018 :hasStewardshipDescription "Check electrolyte levels (especially potassium) during prolonged therapy." .

:SP019 :hasReference :R026 .
:SP019 :hasStewardshipDescription "Monitor sodium levels in patients with heart failure, hypertension, or fluid retention." .

:SP020 :hasReference :R026 .
:SP020 :hasStewardshipDescription "Watch for severe diarrhea that may indicate C. difficile infection." .

:SP021 :hasReference :R026 .
:SP021 :hasStewardshipDescription "Observe for signs of allergic reactions during and after infusion." .

:SP022 :hasReference :R026 .
:SP022 :hasStewardshipDescription "Complete the full prescribed duration even if symptoms improve early." .

:SP023 :hasStewardshipDescription "Use proper infection control practices in hospital settings to prevent the spread of resistant bacteria." .
:SP023 :hasReference :R026 .

:SP024 :hasStewardshipDescription "Avoid unnecessary combination with other nephrotoxic drugs unless clearly needed." .
:SP024 :hasReference :R026 .

:SP025 :hasReference :R027 .
:SP025 :hasStewardshipDescription "Only use Contepo when prescribed by a healthcare professional for a confirmed infection. Avoid using for viral infections like colds or flu." .
:SP025 :hasReference :R028 .

:SP026 :hasReference :R028 .
:SP026 :hasStewardshipDescription "Take infection control measures such as hand hygiene and avoiding contact with sick individuals to prevent the spread of infection." .
:SP026 :hasReference :R027 .

:SP027 :hasStewardshipDescription "Complete the full course of Contepo even if you feel better to prevent bacterial resistance. Do not skip doses." .
:SP027 :hasReference :R027 .
:SP027 :hasReference :R028 .

:SP028 :hasReference :R027 .
:SP028 :hasStewardshipDescription "Report any severe side effects or unusual symptoms to your healthcare provider. Kidney and liver function may need monitorng during treatment." .
:SP028 :hasReference :R028 .

:SP029 :hasReference :R037 .
:SP029 :hasStewardshipDescription "May be taken with meals to reduce gastrointestinal discomfort" .

:SP030 :hasReference :R029 .
:SP030 :hasStewardshipDescription "Only use for prescribed bacterial infections (uncomplicated UTIs). Avoid for viral infections." .
:SP030 :hasReference :R030 .

:SP031 :hasReference :R029 .
:SP031 :hasReference :R030 .
:SP031 :hasStewardshipDescription "Practice good hygiene to reduce infection spread; drink enough fluids." .

:SP032 :hasReference :R030 .
:SP032 :hasStewardshipDescription "Take the full single-dose treatment exactly as prescribed, even if symptoms improve quickly." .
:SP032 :hasReference :R029 .

:SP033 :hasReference :R029 .
:SP033 :hasReference :R030 .
:SP033 :hasStewardshipDescription "Contact your doctor if severe side effects occur. Kidney function may require monitoring." .

:SP034 :hasReference :R038 .
:SP034 :hasStewardshipDescription "For people with advanced HIV infection, to prevent a serious illness called Mycobacterium avium complex (MAC) disease, it can be taken by itself or together with another drug called rifabutin (at the recommended dose)" .

:SP035 :hasStewardshipDescription "For people with advanced HIV infection, to treat a serious illness called Mycobacterium avium complex (MAC) disease, it is taken with another drug called ethambutol (at the recommended dose)" .
:SP035 :hasReference :R038 .

:SP036 :hasReference :R037 .
:SP036 :hasStewardshipDescription "May be taken with or without meals" .

:SP037 :hasStewardshipDescription "Should be swallowed whole with liquid as a single daily dose. Do not chew or crush when taking." .
