:SP143 :hasReference :R092 .
:SP143 :hasStewardshipDescription "In the event of acute overdosage, reversible renal toxicity has been reported in some cases. It is recommended to monitor renal function and to administer magnesium- or calcium-containing antacids which reduce the absorption of ciprofloxacin." .

:SP144 :hasReference :R092 .
:SP144 :hasStewardshipDescription "In the event of acute overdosage, reversible renal toxicity has been reported in some cases. It is recommended to monitor renal function and to administer magnesium- or calcium-containing antacids which reduce the absorption of ciprofloxacin." .

:SP145 :hasReference :R091 .
:SP145 :hasStewardshipDescription "Do not use Ciprofloxacin simulataneously with antacid preparations containing Magnesium Hydroxide or Aluminum Hydrocide. An interval of at least 2 hours must be respected between the administration of an antacid and Ciprofloxacin." .

:SP146 :hasReference :R091 .
:SP146 :hasStewardshipDescription "Patients receiving Ciprofloxacin must be well hydrated to prevent crystalluria. Excessive alkalinisation of urine should be avoided." .

:SP147 :hasReference :R092 .
:SP147 :hasStewardshipDescription "Avoid excessive sunlight" .

:SP148 :hasReference :R092 .
